 focus of the conversation is on what they perceive as disturbing parallels between the 1930s and the recent policy trajectory of the Abe government, in which relations with Japan’s immediate neighbours have seriously deteriorated. The translation is by the distinguished Oxford scholar and author Arthur Stockwin, formerly Director of the Nissan Institute.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aJapan-Politics and government-1989-. 4aAsian Studies. 4aCentral / national / federal government policies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aJapan. 4aPolitics and Government. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Asian.2bisacsh  aconstitution.  ademocracy.  afuture of Japan.1 aJiro, Yamaguchi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJunji, Banno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYamaguchi, Jiro, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066293140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781898823384?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781898823384423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781898823384/original  a978-3-11-066293-1  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK